Explanation of the ML pipeline Flow
1. Input Layer
â€¢	User Speech is captured via microphone.
â€¢	Text Input is supported for accessibility/testing.
â€¢	Upload allows users to provide audio/video/transcripts for persona training.
2. Pre-processing
â€¢	Speech-to-Text (STT): Converts audio to text (Google Cloud STT).
â€¢	Text Cleaning: Normalizes and sanitizes input.
â€¢	Context Builder: Assembles conversation context and prompt for the LLM.
â€¢	Persona Extraction: Learns new personas from uploaded data.
3. ML Pipeline
â€¢	LLM: Generates conversational responses (Qwen2.5-0.5B/GPT-4).
â€¢	Enhanced Response: Post-processes output for persona, tone, and clarity.
â€¢	Fallback: Provides safe responses if the LLM fails.
â€¢	Feedback Generation: Analyzes conversation for performance feedback.
â€¢	Analytics: Tracks metrics and conversation quality.
4. TTS Layer
â€¢	Text-to-Speech: Converts AI text to natural voice (Coqui TTS).
â€¢	Emotion-Aware TTS: (Future) Adds emotional nuance to voice.
5. Model Infrastructure
â€¢	Model Cache: Stores models locally or in the cloud.
â€¢	GPU/CPU Inference: Accelerates model computations.
â€¢	Orchestration: Manages model versions and scaling.
â€¢	Persona DB: Stores persona data for reuse.
â€¢	Audio/Video Storage: Keeps uploaded files for training and review.
6. Output Layer
â€¢	AI Voice Response: Delivered to user for real-time conversation.
â€¢	AI Text Response: For chat interface or transcripts.
â€¢	Performance Feedback: Actionable insights for the user.
â€¢	Session Report: Analytics and improvement suggestions.



